**W3-D7-Relations**

**Today you learn:**
- ForeignKey — one-to-many relationship
- ManyToMany — many-to-many relationship
- Querying both

---

**1. ForeignKey — User has many Posts**

```python
from django.contrib.auth.models import User
from django.db import models

class Post(models.Model):
    title = models.CharField(max_length=200)
    content = models.TextField()
    author = models.ForeignKey(User, on_delete=models.CASCADE)  # links each Post to one User
    # on_delete=CASCADE means: if that User is deleted, delete their Posts too
```

```bash
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
```

---

**2. Create and query ForeignKey**

```python
from django.contrib.auth.models import User
from blog.models import Post

user1 = User.objects.create_user(username="ravi", password="pass123")
Post.objects.create(title="My Post", content="Hello", author=user1)

# query forward - get the author of a post
post = Post.objects.first()
print(post.author.username)

# query backward - get all posts by a user (related_name not set, so default is post_set)
user1.post_set.all()
```

